-- Italy's Banca Carige posts H1 net loss on writedowns, restructuring
-- By Valentina Za
-- Fri Aug 01, 2014 04:16PM EDT
-- None



MILAN, Aug 1 (Reuters) - Italy's Banca Carige <CRGI.MI> posted a first-half net loss of 45.5 million euros ($61 million) due to writedowns on its insurance units, higher taxes and costs to close down branches as part of its restructuring plan.

